\test_input{
\: U+03A3 GREEK CAPITAL LETTER SIGMA maps to
\: U+03C2 GREEK SMALL LETTER FINAL SIGMA when preceded by a Cased character
\: and not followed by a Cased character (Unicode Final_Sigma, section 3.13).
\: Otherwise it maps to U+03C3 GREEK SMALL LETTER SIGMA (non-final form).

\: Sigma at end of string, preceded by a Cased character -> final sigma (U+03C2)
\cowel_str_to_lower("ΑΣ")

\: Lone sigma with nothing cased before it -> non-final sigma (U+03C3)
\cowel_str_to_lower("Σ")

\: Sigma followed by a Cased character -> non-final sigma (U+03C3)
\cowel_str_to_lower("ΣΑ")

\: Sigma at end of a longer word (multiple Cased before) -> final sigma
\cowel_str_to_lower("ΑΒΓΣ")

\: Sigma in the middle of Cased characters (Cased both sides) -> non-final sigma
\cowel_str_to_lower("ΑΒΓΣΔΕΖ")

\: Two consecutive sigmas at the end:
\: first Σ is non-final (followed by another Cased Σ),
\: second Σ is final (nothing Cased after it)
\cowel_str_to_lower("ΑΒΓΣΣ")

\: All sigmas surrounded by Cased characters on both sides -> non-final
\cowel_str_to_lower("ΩΣΣΩ")
}

\test_output{

ας

σ

σα

αβγς

αβγσδεζ

αβγσς

ωσσω
}
